Get up and running with Nx in just a few minutes by following these simple steps.

{% steps %}

1. **Install Nx (optional)**

   You can run Nx immediately with your preferred package manager — no installation required:

   {% tabs syncKey="package-manager" %}
   {% tabitem label="npm" %}

   ```shell
   npx nx@latest --version
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="pnpm" %}

   ```shell
   pnpm dlx nx@latest --version
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="yarn" %}

   ```shell
   yarn dlx nx@latest --version
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="bun" %}

   ```shell
   bunx nx@latest --version
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% /tabs %}

   For frequent use, install globally:

   {% tabs syncKey="install-method" %}
   {% tabitem label="npm" %}

   ```shell
   npm add --global nx
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="Homebrew (macOS, Linux)" %}

   ```shell
   brew install nx
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="Chocolatey (Windows)" %}

   ```shell
   choco install nx
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="apt (Ubuntu)" %}

   ```shell
   sudo add-apt-repository ppa:nrwl/nx
   sudo apt update
   sudo apt install nx
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% /tabs %}

2. **Create or initialize a workspace**

   {% tabs %}
   {% tabitem label="New Project" %}

   Create a new Nx workspace with everything configured:

   {% tabs syncKey="package-manager" %}
   {% tabitem label="npm" %}

   ```shell
   npx create-nx-workspace@latest
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="pnpm" %}

   ```shell
   pnpm create nx-workspace
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="yarn" %}

   ```shell
   yarn create nx-workspace
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="bun" %}

   ```shell
   bunx create-nx-workspace@latest
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% /tabs %}

   Follow the prompts to select your preferred setup and preferences.

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="Existing Project" %}

   Add Nx to any existing repository (works with any language/stack):

   {% tabs syncKey="package-manager" %}
   {% tabitem label="npm" %}

   ```shell
   npx nx@latest init
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="pnpm" %}

   ```shell
   pnpm dlx nx@latest init
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="yarn" %}

   ```shell
   yarn dlx nx@latest init
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% tabitem label="bun" %}

   ```shell
   bunx nx@latest init
   ```

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% /tabs %}

   This adds minimal config and enables caching immediately.

   {% /tabitem %}
   {% /tabs %}

   Learn more: [Start New Project](/docs/getting-started/start-new-project) • [Add to Existing](/docs/getting-started/start-with-existing-project)

3. **Run your first task**

   Run any task with automatic caching:

   ```shell
   nx build my-app      # Build a single project
   nx test my-lib       # Test a single project
   nx run-many -t build test lint   # Run multiple tasks across projects
   ```

   Run it again and watch Nx restore from cache instantly:

   ```shell
   nx build my-app      # ⚡ Cached - completes in milliseconds
   ```

   Explore your workspace with the project graph:

   ```shell
   nx graph
   ```

   Learn more: [Run Tasks](/docs/features/run-tasks) • [Cache Task Results](/docs/features/cache-task-results)

{% /steps %}

